@startuml
title Use Case 8: User Account Creation (IT User)

actor ITUser as "User (IT)"
boundary GUI as "Client GUI"
control Client as "Client App"
control Server as "Server"
collections Cache as "Server Cache\n(User data)"
collections Store as "Server Persistent Storage\n(User records)"

== Open account creation ==
ITUser -> GUI: Select "Create New User Account"
GUI --> ITUser Display form fields\n(name, username, password, role)

== Submit account data ==
ITUser -> GUI: Enter account details\nClick "Create"
GUI -> Client: newUser(User)

Client -> Server: newUser(User)

alt Create rejected (invalid / not permitted / username taken)
Server --> Client: Create failed (reason)
Client -> GUI: Show error message
else Create accepted
Server -> Store: Store new user record
Store --> Server: User stored 
Server -> Cache: Add user to cache
Server --> Client: Create OK 
Client -> Client: Update user list 
Client -> GUI: Show success confirmation\nand new user details
end
@enduml
